12:20.816 --> 12:22.850
Oh, uh, that's tricky.

12:22.850 --> 12:25.052
I'm actually getting married tomorrow.

12:25.052 --> 12:26.288
- Married! Ha!
- Married?

12:26.288 --> 12:27.822
Oh, no, it's not what you think.

12:27.822 --> 12:29.057
It's just so Zoila,

12:29.057 --> 12:30.158
my Guatemalan cleaning lady,

12:30.158 --> 12:31.493
can get her green card.

12:31.493 --> 12:32.894
So it'll be easier for her to send money

12:32.894 --> 12:34.096
back home to her sister

12:34.096 --> 12:35.297
who's in desperate need

12:35.297 --> 12:36.831
of gender reassignment surgery.

12:36.831 --> 12:38.299
Oh!

12:38.299 --> 12:39.768
But hey, that's at 2.

12:39.768 --> 12:40.836
How's 2:30?

12:40.836 --> 12:43.804
*

12:43.804 --> 12:45.006
"Oh, sure, Sue,"

12:45.006 --> 12:46.073
I'll totally help you reconnect

12:46.073 --> 12:47.241
with your dreamy ex-boyfriend.

12:47.241 --> 12:48.376
"That's a good idea."

12:48.376 --> 12:49.811
Idiot!

12:49.811 --> 12:51.746
Guy makes me look like Miss Piggy.

12:51.746 --> 12:53.081
Come on!

12:53.081 --> 12:55.149
Not now.

12:55.149 --> 12:56.250
Oh, come on, unbelievable.

12:56.250 --> 12:58.052
What's next, rain?

12:58.052 --> 12:59.855
(pigeon cooing)

13:02.923 --> 13:03.958
Well, at least one lucky thing

13:03.958 --> 13:06.094
happened today.

13:06.094 --> 13:07.796
Well, well, well,

13:07.796 --> 13:09.464
if it isn't my favorite

13:09.464 --> 13:12.868
sometime collaborator, Mr. Pacalioglu.

13:12.868 --> 13:13.869
- What?
- Oh.

13:13.869 --> 13:15.202
Let me help you here.

13:15.202 --> 13:18.139
Listen, I know we've had our differences

13:18.139 --> 13:19.408
in the past, you and I.

13:19.408 --> 13:20.775
Yeah, you stole my job,

13:20.775 --> 13:22.043
you humiliated me in front of

13:22.043 --> 13:23.345
the New York press, and you made me

13:23.345 --> 13:24.980
look like a dickhead in front of the mayor!

13:24.980 --> 13:25.913
Like I said, we've had

13:25.913 --> 13:27.149
our differences.

13:27.149 --> 13:28.884
But all that is in the past now, isn't it?

13:28.884 --> 13:30.118
- Is it?
- I've got my own

13:30.118 --> 13:31.919
reality TV show in the works

13:31.919 --> 13:33.889
and I'd like to offer you a job.

13:33.889 --> 13:34.956
- A job?
- Mm-hm.

13:34.956 --> 13:38.092
(laughing incredulously)

13:38.092 --> 13:39.394
Something humorous about that?

13:39.394 --> 13:41.462
What? No, no, I'm sorry,

13:41.462 --> 13:42.496
I was thinking about something funny

13:42.496 --> 13:43.532
from earlier.

13:43.532 --> 13:44.899
So you'll take the job?

13:44.899 --> 13:46.868
What in the world do you think

13:46.868 --> 13:48.269
you have to offer me that could make me

13:48.269 --> 13:51.005
want to work for you ever?

13:51.005 --> 13:53.442
I can think of a few things.

13:53.442 --> 13:55.811
*

13:55.811 --> 13:57.846
I'm sorry, Ms. White, but your...

13:57.846 --> 13:59.880
charms no longer hold sway over me.

13:59.880 --> 14:01.950
*

14:01.950 --> 14:03.485
Something in your pants

14:03.485 --> 14:05.019
suggests the contrary.

14:05.019 --> 14:07.022
Oh, that?

14:07.022 --> 14:08.856
I was thinking about something sexy

14:08.856 --> 14:10.491
from earlier.

14:10.491 --> 14:13.128
I gotta go, I gotta go.

14:18.033 --> 14:19.400
So, what, you just ran?

14:19.400 --> 14:21.001
I just ran.

14:21.001 --> 14:23.171
I did like a full bum out, boner jog

14:23.171 --> 14:24.873
but it was like "pew" down the street.

14:24.873 --> 14:26.307
Fast. Tuck and duck.

14:26.307 --> 14:27.542
Yeah, she was in my boner dust.

14:27.542 --> 14:29.009
I'm proud of you, man.

14:29.009 --> 14:30.312
You practiced some restraint, that's dope.

14:30.312 --> 14:31.346
You know, and maybe this means

14:31.346 --> 14:32.913
I'm finally over Camomile White

14:32.913 --> 14:34.149
or at the very least,

14:34.149 --> 14:35.549
I've gotten really good at lying to myself

14:35.549 --> 14:36.350
about being over her.

14:36.350 --> 14:37.818
So, either way.

14:37.818 --> 14:38.919
Yo, speaking of lies, how's it going

14:38.919 --> 14:40.020
with your little ghost boo?

14:40.020 --> 14:41.155
Uh...

14:41.155 --> 14:43.325
The ghost boo, lies situation

14:43.325 --> 14:45.427
is not going very well, I fear.

14:45.427 --> 14:46.894
I am now being asked to help her

14:46.894 --> 14:50.131
get closure with her ex-boyfriend.

14:50.131 --> 14:51.732
So, man up.

14:51.732 --> 14:52.767
Help her get closure, Pac.

14:52.767 --> 14:54.235
I know, it's just that

14:54.235 --> 14:56.471
there's not any real closure to be had.

14:56.471 --> 14:57.905
And now the more that these two talk

14:57.905 --> 14:58.907
to each other, the deeper she falls

14:58.907 --> 15:00.341
under his nice guy spell.

15:00.341 --> 15:02.009
Time out, you listening
to what you're saying?

15:02.009 --> 15:04.044
You're saying the more they talk, right?

15:04.044 --> 15:05.212
Like, you the one running the show.

15:05.212 --> 15:06.214
You the only one that can hear.

15:06.214 --> 15:07.349
Unless this guy develop

15:07.349 --> 15:08.450
a talent for hearing ghosts,

15:08.450 --> 15:09.384
then as far as I see it

15:09.384 --> 15:10.451
you good, baby.

15:10.451 --> 15:12.287
'Cause he's not, he's not gonna.

15:12.287 --> 15:13.455
Closure, you know?

15:13.455 --> 15:14.889
Okay, I got it.

15:14.889 --> 15:18.025
*

15:18.025 --> 15:19.193
No, no, I got it.

15:19.193 --> 15:22.230
*

15:22.230 --> 15:23.831
That felt exotic.

15:23.831 --> 15:25.866
What? Glen.

15:25.866 --> 15:29.070
You died? What the hell, man?

15:31.754 --> 15:32.788
Craziest thing.

15:32.788 --> 15:34.256
I go into the bathroom

15:34.256 --> 15:35.625
to take a bowel movement,

15:35.625 --> 15:36.926
I slip on a huge puddle of water,

15:36.926 --> 15:38.628
crack my head wide open.

15:38.628 --> 15:39.663
Yeah, I guess I forgot to tuck

15:39.663 --> 15:41.264
the liner into the tub

15:41.264 --> 15:42.865
before my last shower.

15:42.865 --> 15:44.500
Yeah, yeah.

15:44.500 --> 15:46.536
But hey, on the bright side,

15:46.536 --> 15:49.338
now I can talk to Sue without a translator.

15:49.338 --> 15:50.407
Looks like we can make that date

15:50.407 --> 15:51.441
work without you.

15:51.441 --> 15:53.710
Oh good, everybody wins.

15:53.710 --> 15:55.412
Everyone except Zoila.

15:55.412 --> 15:56.613
I'm sorry, who?

15:56.613 --> 15:57.880
My Guatemalan cleaning lady.

15:57.880 --> 15:59.349
Oh, yeah.

15:59.349 --> 16:00.649
Not being able to

16:00.649 --> 16:02.284
give her that green card will be

16:02.284 --> 16:04.888
the biggest regret of my life.

16:04.888 --> 16:06.655
The one thing I left unfinished.

16:06.655 --> 16:08.457
*

16:08.457 --> 16:10.493
But what are you gonna do?

16:10.493 --> 16:12.495
I don't know.

16:12.495 --> 16:13.897
All right, well, I'm off

16:13.897 --> 16:15.565
to my date.

16:16.799 --> 16:20.799
*

16:21.738 --> 16:23.405
So you want me to tail this guy?

16:23.405 --> 16:25.508
Well, I can't bloody do it, can I?

16:25.508 --> 16:26.676
He knows me.

16:26.676 --> 16:28.977
I'm a famous television actor.

16:28.977 --> 16:29.979
Yes.

16:29.979 --> 16:31.681
A famous, brilliant

16:31.681 --> 16:32.716
television actor

16:32.716 --> 16:34.918
who plays a detective.

16:34.918 --> 16:38.620
A strong, smart detective,

16:38.620 --> 16:41.323
who always gets his man.

16:41.323 --> 16:43.659
Or woman. Sorry.

16:43.659 --> 16:44.927
I mean, we just,

16:44.927 --> 16:46.962
we are very careful on the show

16:46.962 --> 16:49.365
to portray women as criminals too.

16:49.365 --> 16:52.501
Be that detective, Matthew.

16:52.501 --> 16:54.236
For me.

16:55.739 --> 16:57.373
So, I know you had your heart

16:57.373 --> 16:58.741
set on marrying Glen,

16:58.741 --> 17:01.344
but for the before-mentioned reasons,

17:01.344 --> 17:02.445
it ain't gonna happen.

17:02.445 --> 17:03.846
Lo siento.

17:03.846 --> 17:05.582
No Inglés.

17:05.582 --> 17:06.982
Let's see, how do I put this

17:06.982 --> 17:08.684
delicately?

17:08.684 --> 17:09.853
Uh, Mr. Glen...

17:09.853 --> 17:11.954
Sí, sí, Mr. Glen.

17:11.954 --> 17:13.355
(whistling)

17:13.355 --> 17:14.423
Whoop!

17:14.423 --> 17:16.425
(imitating crashing sounds)

17:16.425 --> 17:18.027
Oh no!

17:18.027 --> 17:20.695
No! Mr. Glen!

17:20.695 --> 17:21.931
I know, Mr. Glen,

17:21.931 --> 17:23.266
but... yeah, yeah, but, you know what,

17:23.266 --> 17:24.467
it's okay.

17:24.467 --> 17:25.602
It's okay, because you know why?

17:25.602 --> 17:28.238
'Cause I'm gonna marry you.

17:28.238 --> 17:29.939
I will marry you.

17:29.939 --> 17:31.775
*

17:31.775 --> 17:34.376
Zoila, look, look, I...

17:34.376 --> 17:35.944
Zoila.

17:35.944 --> 17:37.881
(spits)

17:37.881 --> 17:39.516
Will you do me the honor of letting me

17:39.516 --> 17:41.416
be the number one man in your life?

17:41.416 --> 17:42.551
¿Tú?

17:42.551 --> 17:43.752
Yeah, okay, number two man

17:43.752 --> 17:45.355
in your life, Glen was option A,

17:45.355 --> 17:47.624
I'm option B, obviously.

17:49.291 --> 17:50.425
Sí.

17:50.425 --> 17:52.662
All right, yeah, option C, fine.

17:52.662 --> 17:54.364
Whatever, do you want a green card or not?

17:54.364 --> 17:56.398
Oh, espera, espera.

18:02.471 --> 18:03.573
We need to provide proof

18:03.573 --> 18:05.441
of a meaningful relationship?

18:05.441 --> 18:07.743
That could take hours!

18:07.743 --> 18:11.743
*

18:15.818 --> 18:17.720
(camera clicking)

18:17.720 --> 18:21.720
*

18:40.742 --> 18:42.612
_

18:42.612 --> 18:43.947
You have the necessary paperwork

18:43.947 --> 18:45.414
and proof of relationship?

18:45.414 --> 18:47.383
Yes, of course.

18:47.383 --> 18:48.518
There you go.

18:48.518 --> 18:50.586
Should all be accounted for.

18:50.586 --> 18:54.586
*

18:57.993 --> 19:00.596
How did you two like Paris?

19:00.596 --> 19:02.832
Fine. Expensive.

19:02.832 --> 19:05.500
And how'd you two like the moon?

19:05.500 --> 19:09.500
*

19:12.976 --> 19:15.778
Good. It was warm.

19:15.778 --> 19:17.779
- The moon was warm?
- Yeah, really warm.

19:17.779 --> 19:19.481
Unseasonably warm.

19:19.481 --> 19:20.782
That's why I was so sweaty.

19:20.782 --> 19:22.251
Yeah, I took that picture

19:22.251 --> 19:23.519
at the National Air and Space Museum

19:23.519 --> 19:26.422
in D.C. two Labor Days ago.

19:26.422 --> 19:27.856
It was hot as hell, right?

19:27.856 --> 19:29.325
- Roofie, you made it.
- I know.

19:29.325 --> 19:30.593
I thought you might need a witness.

19:30.593 --> 19:34.593
*

19:37.366 --> 19:38.835
One last question.

19:38.835 --> 19:41.770
Since she clearly can't speak English,

19:41.770 --> 19:44.606
I take it you can speak Spanish?

19:44.606 --> 19:46.241
Sí.

19:46.241 --> 19:47.844
Sí.

19:47.844 --> 19:50.947
- See?
- Mm-hm.

19:50.947 --> 19:53.682
Good enough for me.

19:53.682 --> 19:54.917
_

19:54.917 --> 19:58.917
*

20:08.730 --> 20:10.900
(boat horn blowing)

20:11.934 --> 20:14.237
Hey! Hey. Hi, Sue!

20:14.237 --> 20:15.404
I am so sorry I'm late.

20:15.404 --> 20:16.772
I got a little hung up

20:16.772 --> 20:20.343
but, uh, did Glen ever show up or... ?

20:20.343 --> 20:21.411
Actually, he did.

20:21.411 --> 20:22.377
Yeah?

20:22.377 --> 20:23.413
As a ghost.

20:23.413 --> 20:25.414
As a what? As a ghost?

20:25.414 --> 20:26.449
It was crazy.

20:26.449 --> 20:27.549
That is crazy.

20:27.549 --> 20:28.684
But as soon as he saw me,

20:28.684 --> 20:30.286
he turned into energy

20:30.286 --> 20:31.554
and went into his light.

20:31.554 --> 20:32.689
Oh, well, look, Sue,

20:32.689 --> 20:34.557
I know that you were...

20:34.557 --> 20:35.892
really jazzed about getting back together

20:35.892 --> 20:36.960
with Glen or whatever.

20:36.960 --> 20:38.327
What? No I wasn't.

20:38.327 --> 20:39.561
What, you weren't?

20:39.561 --> 20:41.263
No, I just thought that having him show up

20:41.263 --> 20:43.900
for this date was my unfinished business.

20:43.900 --> 20:44.968
Turns out it wasn't,

20:44.968 --> 20:47.336
it was his.

20:47.336 --> 20:50.373
All these attempts to
figure out why I'm a ghost,

20:50.373 --> 20:54.242
they just end in disappointment.

20:54.242 --> 20:55.877
I, all right, Sue, listen...

20:55.877 --> 20:57.480
No wait, let me finish.

20:57.480 --> 21:00.249
I realized something.

21:00.249 --> 21:01.817
Going into the light

21:01.817 --> 21:03.618
will happen when it's supposed to happen.

21:03.618 --> 21:06.489
There's no use in obsessing over it.

21:06.489 --> 21:08.557
That's why I decided I'm gonna start

21:08.557 --> 21:09.625
living in the moment.

21:09.625 --> 21:10.926
That's good.

21:10.926 --> 21:12.528
I got a pretty good thing right here.

21:12.528 --> 21:14.396
You're talking about me, right?

21:14.396 --> 21:16.432
*

21:16.432 --> 21:18.567
(clears throat)

21:18.567 --> 21:19.701
All right, come on, let's go.

21:19.701 --> 21:21.237
Let's get outta here.

21:21.237 --> 21:25.237
*

21:26.909 --> 21:29.644
Oh, by the way, I hired a new housekeeper.

21:29.644 --> 21:32.448
Just ignore her, okay?

21:32.448 --> 21:33.548
Whoop, oh, I just walked you

21:33.548 --> 21:34.683
through a chair.

21:34.683 --> 21:36.551
(chuckling)

21:40.990 --> 21:44.059
*

21:44.059 --> 21:47.096
Well, all right, I tailed him all day

21:47.096 --> 21:48.530
and I gotta say, Cam,

21:48.530 --> 21:49.765
I feel like one of your assistants.

21:49.765 --> 21:50.833
Don't be silly, you're just being

21:50.833 --> 21:52.101
a really good boyfriend.

21:52.101 --> 21:53.536
If this is what your boyfriends do,

21:53.536 --> 21:54.970
you are the most high maintenance

21:54.970 --> 21:56.505
girlfriend I've ever had.

21:56.505 --> 21:57.673
What is that, chicken?

21:57.673 --> 21:59.541
Swan.

21:59.541 --> 22:01.042
Anyway, here. I didn't hear much,

22:01.042 --> 22:02.077
but I think he was on a Bluetooth

22:02.077 --> 22:03.211
talking to his lawyer.

